explanation: The solution iterates through all possible factors of n. If a factor is found, it decrements a counter. When the counter reaches zero, the current factor is returned as the kth factor. If the loop completes without finding the kth factor, -1 is returned.  This approach has a time complexity of O(n) as it iterates through all potential factors.  It has a space complexity of O(1) as it uses a constant amount of extra space.

